{
  "stem": "9503.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She practiced some of it out of form, but not out of intent.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She kept a kosher home after the war, but it was for my uncle, not for herself.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] some of these experiences, I think, are, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to me, are-- indicate much more of a suffering than the daily-- the food, the-- the cold, the heat, whatever.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's like episodes like that-- that-- that keep on coming up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- I was really-- I was disappointed in my mother, who was a wonderful woman and practical.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Could you describe a little bit about the hygiene in the camp?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they had these long, like, troughs with cold water, and you sort of had to elbow your way to a faucet to do some washing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somehow or other, to me, it didn't seem to be that important, and I really wonder how much I washed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't remember a toothbrush.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember that, once I lived in the orphanage, I could see my mother only one day a week.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the camp was-- was just rampant with lice and fleas and stuff like that, and if you had lice, your hair got shorn.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother took pride in my hair.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That must, to her-- that must have been, to her, her chance of mothering.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because every week that I saw her, that I had a chance to be with her, she would insist on going through my hair with a fine-toothed comb.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the hair was snarled and knotted, and it didn't feel good, and I dreaded it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I actually dreaded seeing my mother because that fine-toothed comb would come out.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
